"title": "5092: Elijah",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5092: elijah",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Living in Israel, his ministry as a prophet was to oppose the worship of Baal in Israel, and the sin, injustices and idolatry of Ahab, Jezebel and Ahaziah. He came, probably, from Tishbe in Gilead, but his parentage is not certain. His name means “the LORD is God”.</p>\n<h2>Elijah's special standing as a prophet</h2>\n<h3>His prophecies and prayers were fulfilled and attested by miracles</h3>\n<p>Drought prophesied and experienced:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:1\">1KI 17:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:7\">1KI 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:1-1Kgs18:6\">1KI 18:1–18:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:17\">JAS 5:17</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:14\">1KI 17:14</a> <em>provision of flour and oil prophesied</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:41\">1KI 18:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:44-1Kgs18:45\">1KI 18:44–18:45</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:17-1Kgs17:24\">1KI 17:17–17:24</a> <em>The widow's son is restored to life.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36-1Kgs18:38\">1KI 18:36–18:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:10\">2KI 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:12\">2KI 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:20-1Kgs21:24\">1KI 21:20–21:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:37-1Kgs22:38\">1KI 22:37–22:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:30-2Kgs9:37\">2KI 9:30–9:37</a></p>\n<h3>The word of the LORD came to him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:9-1Kgs19:18\">1KI 19:9–19:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:8\">1KI 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:1\">1KI 18:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:17\">1KI 21:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:23\">1KI 21:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:28\">1KI 21:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:38\">1KI 22:38</a></p>\n<h2>Elijah's ministry to Israel</h2>\n<h3>He confronts Ahab, king of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:16-1Kgs18:18\">1KI 18:16–18:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:20-1Kgs21:22\">1KI 21:20–21:22</a></p>\n<h3>He challenges the people of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He challenges Baal and his prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:20-1Kgs18:29\">1KI 18:20–18:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36-1Kgs18:38\">1KI 18:36–18:38</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The prophets of Baal are sentenced to death and executed</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:40\">1KI 18:40</a></p>\n<h3>Elijah calls down fire on Ahaziah's messengers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:1-2Kgs1:14\">2KI 1:1–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>He predicts Ahaziah's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:16-2Kgs1:17\">2KI 1:16–1:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He appoints successors to continue the fight against Baal worshippers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:15-1Kgs19:17\">1KI 19:15–19:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:19-1Kgs19:21\">1KI 19:19–19:21</a> <em>Elisha is called</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:13-2Kgs8:15\">2KI 8:13–8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:1-2Kgs9:13\">2KI 9:1–9:13</a> <em>Jehu is anointed by one of Elisha's assistants.</em></p>\n<h2>He does not die, but is taken up to heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:11-2Kgs2:12\">2KI 2:11–2:12</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Elijah's lifestyle and character</h2>\n<h3>It was one of simplicity</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:2-1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:2–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:4-1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:4–19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:8\">2KI 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>He was a man of action and physical endurance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:1\">1KI 17:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:3\">1KI 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:9\">1KI 17:9</a></p>\n<h2>Parallels between Elijah and Moses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:8\">2KI 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:21-Exod14:22\">EXO 14:21–14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:14-Josh3:17\">JOS 3:14–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:14\">2KI 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Elijah's return is awaited by Israel</h2>\n<h3>Some Jews believed John the Baptist was Elijah returned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:17\">LUK 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:5-Mal4:6\">MAL 4:5–4:6</a>MAT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal11:14\">11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:9-Matt17:13\">MAT 17:9–17:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:9-Mark9:13\">MRK 9:9–9:13</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:21\">JHN 1:21</a> <em>John the Baptist denies being Elijah.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:8\">2KI 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:4\">MAT 3:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:6\">MRK 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Elijah appears at the transfiguration of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1-Matt17:8\">MAT 17:1–17:8</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2-Mark9:8\">MRK 9:2–9:8</a></p>",
